The development of a gas market in Albania is a must and will allow the country to:
 Develop a policy for security of supply,;
 Increase the number of participants in the local market;
 Attract investments in the gas sector;
 Improve retail market efficiency;
 Improve system operations;
 Become part of regional gas market;
 Improve economic development with potential regional trading hub.

Challenges in gas sector include:
 Large investment needed for the development of the domestic gas system;
 Lack of a proper market-based environment for attraction of private investors in gas sector;
 Competitiveness of natural gas or the economics of fuel source switching;
 Complete market opening through the establishment of functioning traded markets;
 Market size and sustainability.;
